2233/// Release the given object.
2234/// call void \@objc_release(i8* %value)
2235void CodeGenFunction::EmitARCRelease(llvm::Value *value,
2236 ARCPreciseLifetime_t precise) {
2237 if (isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(value)) return;
2238
2239 llvm::Function *&fn = CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_release;
2240 if (!fn) {
2241 fn = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::objc_release);
2242 setARCRuntimeFunctionLinkage(CGM, fn);
2243 }
2244
2245 // Cast the argument to 'id'.
2246 value = Builder.CreateBitCast(value, Int8PtrTy);
2247
2248 // Call objc_release.
2249 llvm::CallInst *call = EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(fn, value);
2250
2251 if (precise == ARCImpreciseLifetime) {
2252 call->setMetadata("clang.imprecise_release",
2253 llvm::MDNode::get(Builder.getContext(), None));
2254 }
2255}

2257/// Destroy a __strong variable.
2258///
2259/// At -O0, emit a call to store 'null' into the address;
2260/// instrumenting tools prefer this because the address is exposed,
2261/// but it's relatively cumbersome to optimize.
2262///
2263/// At -O1 and above, just load and call objc_release.
2264///
2265/// call void \@objc_storeStrong(i8** %addr, i8* null)
2266void CodeGenFunction::EmitARCDestroyStrong(Address addr,
2267 ARCPreciseLifetime_t precise) {
2268 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel == 0) {
2269 llvm::Value *null = getNullForVariable(addr);
2270 EmitARCStoreStrongCall(addr, null, /*ignored*/ true);
2271 return;
2272 }
2273
2274 llvm::Value *value = Builder.CreateLoad(addr);
2275 EmitARCRelease(value, precise);
2276}

2301/// Store into a strong object. Sometimes calls this:
2302/// call void \@objc_storeStrong(i8** %addr, i8* %value)
2303/// Other times, breaks it down into components.
2304llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARCStoreStrong(LValue dst,
2305 llvm::Value *newValue,
2306 bool ignored) {
2307 QualType type = dst.getType();
2308 bool isBlock = type->isBlockPointerType();
2309
2310 // Use a store barrier at -O0 unless this is a block type or the
2311 // lvalue is inadequately aligned.
2312 if (shouldUseFusedARCCalls() &&
2313 !isBlock &&
2314 (dst.getAlignment().isZero() ||
2315 dst.getAlignment() >= CharUnits::fromQuantity(PointerAlignInBytes))) {
2316 return EmitARCStoreStrongCall(dst.getAddress(), newValue, ignored);
2317 }
2318
2319 // Otherwise, split it out.
2320
2321 // Retain the new value.
2322 newValue = EmitARCRetain(type, newValue);
2323
2324 // Read the old value.
2325 llvm::Value *oldValue = EmitLoadOfScalar(dst, SourceLocation());
2326
2327 // Store. We do this before the release so that any deallocs won't
2328 // see the old value.
2329 EmitStoreOfScalar(newValue, dst);
2330
2331 // Finally, release the old value.
2332 EmitARCRelease(oldValue, dst.isARCPreciseLifetime());
2333
2334 return newValue;
2335}

2408/// i8* \@objc_storeWeak(i8** %addr, i8* %value)
2409/// Returns %value.
2410llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARCStoreWeak(Address addr,
2411 llvm::Value *value,
2412 bool ignored) {
2413 return emitARCStoreOperation(*this, addr, value,
2414 CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_storeWeak,
2415 llvm::Intrinsic::objc_storeWeak, ignored);
2416}
2417
2418/// i8* \@objc_initWeak(i8** %addr, i8* %value)
2419/// Returns %value. %addr is known to not have a current weak entry.
2420/// Essentially equivalent to:
2421/// *addr = nil; objc_storeWeak(addr, value);
2422void CodeGenFunction::EmitARCInitWeak(Address addr, llvm::Value *value) {
2423 // If we're initializing to null, just write null to memory; no need
2424 // to get the runtime involved. But don't do this if optimization
2425 // is enabled, because accounting for this would make the optimizer
2426 // much more complicated.
2427 if (isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(value) &&
2428 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel == 0) {
2429 Builder.CreateStore(value, addr);
2430 return;
2431 }
2432
2433 emitARCStoreOperation(*this, addr, value,
2434 CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_initWeak,
2435 llvm::Intrinsic::objc_initWeak, /*ignored*/ true);
2436}
2437
2438/// void \@objc_destroyWeak(i8** %addr)
2439/// Essentially objc_storeWeak(addr, nil).
2440void CodeGenFunction::EmitARCDestroyWeak(Address addr) {
2441 llvm::Function *&fn = CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_destroyWeak;
2442 if (!fn) {
2443 fn = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::objc_destroyWeak);
2444 setARCRuntimeFunctionLinkage(CGM, fn);
2445 }
2446
2447 // Cast the argument to 'id*'.
2448 addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(addr, Int8PtrPtrTy);
2449
2450 EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(fn, addr.getPointer());
2451}
2452
2453/// void \@objc_moveWeak(i8** %dest, i8** %src)
2454/// Disregards the current value in %dest. Leaves %src pointing to nothing.
2455/// Essentially (objc_copyWeak(dest, src), objc_destroyWeak(src)).
2456void CodeGenFunction::EmitARCMoveWeak(Address dst, Address src) {
2457 emitARCCopyOperation(*this, dst, src,
2458 CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_moveWeak,
2459 llvm::Intrinsic::objc_moveWeak);
2460}
2461
2462/// void \@objc_copyWeak(i8** %dest, i8** %src)
2463/// Disregards the current value in %dest. Essentially
2464/// objc_release(objc_initWeak(dest, objc_readWeakRetained(src)))
2465void CodeGenFunction::EmitARCCopyWeak(Address dst, Address src) {
2466 emitARCCopyOperation(*this, dst, src,
2467 CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_copyWeak,
2468 llvm::Intrinsic::objc_copyWeak);
2469}

2471void CodeGenFunction::emitARCCopyAssignWeak(QualType Ty, Address DstAddr,
2472 Address SrcAddr) {
2473 llvm::Value *Object = EmitARCLoadWeakRetained(SrcAddr);
2474 Object = EmitObjCConsumeObject(Ty, Object);
2475 EmitARCStoreWeak(DstAddr, Object, false);
2476}

2478void CodeGenFunction::emitARCMoveAssignWeak(QualType Ty, Address DstAddr,
2479 Address SrcAddr) {

2481 Object = EmitObjCConsumeObject(Ty, Object);

2498/// Produce the code to do a primitive release.
2499/// call void \@objc_autoreleasePoolPop(i8* %ptr)
2500void CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCAutoreleasePoolPop(llvm::Value *value) {
2501 assert(value->getType() == Int8PtrTy);
2502
2503 if (getInvokeDest()) {
2504 // Call the runtime method not the intrinsic if we are handling exceptions
2505 llvm::FunctionCallee &fn =
2506 CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_autoreleasePoolPopInvoke;
2507 if (!fn) {
2508 llvm::FunctionType *fnType =
2509 llvm::FunctionType::get(Builder.getVoidTy(), Int8PtrTy, false);
2510 fn = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(fnType, "objc_autoreleasePoolPop");
2511 setARCRuntimeFunctionLinkage(CGM, fn);
2512 }
2513
2514 // objc_autoreleasePoolPop can throw.
2515 EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(fn, value);
2516 } else {
2517 llvm::FunctionCallee &fn = CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_autoreleasePoolPop;
2518 if (!fn) {
2519 fn = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::objc_autoreleasePoolPop);
2520 setARCRuntimeFunctionLinkage(CGM, fn);
2521 }
2522
2523 EmitRuntimeCall(fn, value);
2524 }
2525}
2526
2527/// Produce the code to do an MRR version objc_autoreleasepool_push.
2528/// Which is: [[NSAutoreleasePool alloc] init];
2529/// Where alloc is declared as: + (id) alloc; in NSAutoreleasePool class.
2530/// init is declared as: - (id) init; in its NSObject super class.
2531///
2532llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCMRRAutoreleasePoolPush() {
2533 CGObjCRuntime &Runtime = CGM.getObjCRuntime();
2534 llvm::Value *Receiver = Runtime.EmitNSAutoreleasePoolClassRef(*this);
2535 // [NSAutoreleasePool alloc]
2536 IdentifierInfo *II = &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("alloc");
2537 Selector AllocSel = getContext().Selectors.getSelector(0, &II);
2538 CallArgList Args;
2539 RValue AllocRV =
2540 Runtime.GenerateMessageSend(*this, ReturnValueSlot(),
2541 getContext().getObjCIdType(),
2542 AllocSel, Receiver, Args);
2543
2544 // [Receiver init]
2545 Receiver = AllocRV.getScalarVal();
2546 II = &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("init");
2547 Selector InitSel = getContext().Selectors.getSelector(0, &II);
2548 RValue InitRV =
2549 Runtime.GenerateMessageSend(*this, ReturnValueSlot(),
2550 getContext().getObjCIdType(),
2551 InitSel, Receiver, Args);
2552 return InitRV.getScalarVal();
2553}

2633/// Release the given object.
2634/// call void \@objc_release(i8* %value)
2635void CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCRelease(llvm::Value *value,
2636 ARCPreciseLifetime_t precise) {
2637 if (isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(value)) return;
2638
2639 llvm::FunctionCallee &fn =
2640 CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_releaseRuntimeFunction;
2641 if (!fn) {
2642 llvm::FunctionType *fnType =
2643 llvm::FunctionType::get(Builder.getVoidTy(), Int8PtrTy, false);
2644 fn = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(fnType, "objc_release");
2645 setARCRuntimeFunctionLinkage(CGM, fn);
2646 // We have Native ARC, so set nonlazybind attribute for performance
2647 if (llvm::Function *f = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(fn.getCallee()))
2648 f->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonLazyBind);
2649 }
2650
2651 // Cast the argument to 'id'.
2652 value = Builder.CreateBitCast(value, Int8PtrTy);
2653
2654 // Call objc_release.
2655 llvm::CallBase *call = EmitCallOrInvoke(fn, value);
2656
2657 if (precise == ARCImpreciseLifetime) {
2658 call->setMetadata("clang.imprecise_release",
2659 llvm::MDNode::get(Builder.getContext(), None));
2660 }
2661}

2691static bool shouldRetainObjCLifetime(Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lifetime) {
2692 switch (lifetime) {
2693 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
2694 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2695 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2696 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
2697 return true;
2698
2699 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2700 return false;
2701 }
2702
2703 llvm_unreachable("impossible lifetime!");
2704}
2705
2706static TryEmitResult tryEmitARCRetainLoadOfScalar(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2707 LValue lvalue,
2708 QualType type) {
2709 llvm::Value *result;
2710 bool shouldRetain = shouldRetainObjCLifetime(type.getObjCLifetime());
2711 if (shouldRetain) {
2712 result = CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(lvalue, SourceLocation()).getScalarVal();
2713 } else {
2714 assert(type.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak);
2715 result = CGF.EmitARCLoadWeakRetained(lvalue.getAddress());
2716 }
2717 return TryEmitResult(result, !shouldRetain);
2718}
2719
2720static TryEmitResult tryEmitARCRetainLoadOfScalar(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2721 const Expr *e) {
2722 e = e->IgnoreParens();
2723 QualType type = e->getType();
2724
2725 // If we're loading retained from a __strong xvalue, we can avoid
2726 // an extra retain/release pair by zeroing out the source of this
2727 // "move" operation.
2728 if (e->isXValue() &&
2729 !type.isConstQualified() &&
2730 type.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
2731 // Emit the lvalue.
2732 LValue lv = CGF.EmitLValue(e);
2733
2734 // Load the object pointer.
2735 llvm::Value *result = CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(lv,
2736 SourceLocation()).getScalarVal();
2737
2738 // Set the source pointer to NULL.
2739 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(getNullForVariable(lv.getAddress()), lv);
2740
2741 return TryEmitResult(result, true);
2742 }
2743
2744 // As a very special optimization, in ARC++, if the l-value is the
2745 // result of a non-volatile assignment, do a simple retain of the
2746 // result of the call to objc_storeWeak instead of reloading.
2747 if (CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
2748 !type.isVolatileQualified() &&
2749 type.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak &&
2750 isa<BinaryOperator>(e) &&
2751 cast<BinaryOperator>(e)->getOpcode() == BO_Assign)
2752 return TryEmitResult(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(e), false);
2753
2754 // Try to emit code for scalar constant instead of emitting LValue and
2755 // loading it because we are not guaranteed to have an l-value. One of such
2756 // cases is DeclRefExpr referencing non-odr-used constant-evaluated variable.
2757 if (const auto *decl_expr = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(e)) {
2758 auto *DRE = const_cast<DeclRefExpr *>(decl_expr);
2759 if (CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission constant = CGF.tryEmitAsConstant(DRE))
2760 return TryEmitResult(CGF.emitScalarConstant(constant, DRE),
2761 !shouldRetainObjCLifetime(type.getObjCLifetime()));
2762 }
2763
2764 return tryEmitARCRetainLoadOfScalar(CGF, CGF.EmitLValue(e), type);
2765}
2766
2767typedef llvm::function_ref<llvm::Value *(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2768 llvm::Value *value)>
2769 ValueTransform;
2770
2771/// Insert code immediately after a call.
2772static llvm::Value *emitARCOperationAfterCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2773 llvm::Value *value,
2774 ValueTransform doAfterCall,
2775 ValueTransform doFallback) {
2776 if (llvm::CallInst *call = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(value)) {
2777 CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint ip = CGF.Builder.saveIP();
2778
2779 // Place the retain immediately following the call.
2780 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(call->getParent(),
2781 ++llvm::BasicBlock::iterator(call));
2782 value = doAfterCall(CGF, value);
2783
2784 CGF.Builder.restoreIP(ip);
2785 return value;
2786 } else if (llvm::InvokeInst *invoke = dyn_cast<llvm::InvokeInst>(value)) {
2787 CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint ip = CGF.Builder.saveIP();
2788
2789 // Place the retain at the beginning of the normal destination block.
2790 llvm::BasicBlock *BB = invoke->getNormalDest();
2791 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(BB, BB->begin());
2792 value = doAfterCall(CGF, value);
2793
2794 CGF.Builder.restoreIP(ip);
2795 return value;
2796
2797 // Bitcasts can arise because of related-result returns. Rewrite
2798 // the operand.
2799 } else if (llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(value)) {
2800 llvm::Value *operand = bitcast->getOperand(0);
2801 operand = emitARCOperationAfterCall(CGF, operand, doAfterCall, doFallback);
2802 bitcast->setOperand(0, operand);
2803 return bitcast;
2804
2805 // Generic fall-back case.
2806 } else {
2807 // Retain using the non-block variant: we never need to do a copy
2808 // of a block that's been returned to us.
2809 return doFallback(CGF, value);
2810 }
2811}

2813/// Given that the given expression is some sort of call (which does
2814/// not return retained), emit a retain following it.
2815static llvm::Value *emitARCRetainCallResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2816 const Expr *e) {
2817 llvm::Value *value = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(e);
2818 return emitARCOperationAfterCall(CGF, value,

2820 return CGF.EmitARCRetainAutoreleasedReturnValue(value);
2821 },
2822 [](CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *value) {
2823 return CGF.EmitARCRetainNonBlock(value);
2824 });
2825}

2841llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARCReclaimReturnedObject(const Expr *E,

2852/// Determine whether it might be important to emit a separate
2853/// objc_retain_block on the result of the given expression, or
2854/// whether it's okay to just emit it in a +1 context.
2855static bool shouldEmitSeparateBlockRetain(const Expr *e) {
2856 assert(e->getType()->isBlockPointerType());
2857 e = e->IgnoreParens();
2858
2859 // For future goodness, emit block expressions directly in +1
2860 // contexts if we can.
2861 if (isa<BlockExpr>(e))
2862 return false;
2863
2864 if (const CastExpr *cast = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(e)) {
2865 switch (cast->getCastKind()) {
2866 // Emitting these operations in +1 contexts is goodness.
2867 case CK_LValueToRValue:
2868 case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
2869 case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
2870 case CK_ARCProduceObject:
2871 return false;
2872
2873 // These operations preserve a block type.
2874 case CK_NoOp:
2875 case CK_BitCast:
2876 return shouldEmitSeparateBlockRetain(cast->getSubExpr());
2877
2878 // These operations are known to be bad (or haven't been considered).
2879 case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
2880 default:
2881 return true;
2882 }
2883 }
2884
2885 return true;
2886}

2888namespace {
2889/// A CRTP base class for emitting expressions of retainable object
2890/// pointer type in ARC.
2891template <typename Impl, typename Result> class ARCExprEmitter {
2892protected:
2893 CodeGenFunction &CGF;
2894 Impl &asImpl() { return *static_cast<Impl*>(this); }
2895
2896 ARCExprEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF) : CGF(CGF) {}
2897
2898public:
2899 Result visit(const Expr *e);
2900 Result visitCastExpr(const CastExpr *e);
2901 Result visitPseudoObjectExpr(const PseudoObjectExpr *e);
2902 Result visitBlockExpr(const BlockExpr *e);
2903 Result visitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *e);
2904 Result visitBinAssign(const BinaryOperator *e);
2905 Result visitBinAssignUnsafeUnretained(const BinaryOperator *e);
2906 Result visitBinAssignAutoreleasing(const BinaryOperator *e);
2907 Result visitBinAssignWeak(const BinaryOperator *e);
2908 Result visitBinAssignStrong(const BinaryOperator *e);
2909
2910 // Minimal implementation:
2911 // Result visitLValueToRValue(const Expr *e)
2912 // Result visitConsumeObject(const Expr *e)
2913 // Result visitExtendBlockObject(const Expr *e)
2914 // Result visitReclaimReturnedObject(const Expr *e)
2915 // Result visitCall(const Expr *e)
2916 // Result visitExpr(const Expr *e)
2917 //
2918 // Result emitBitCast(Result result, llvm::Type *resultType)
2919 // llvm::Value *getValueOfResult(Result result)
2920};
2921}
2922
2923/// Try to emit a PseudoObjectExpr under special ARC rules.
2924///
2925/// This massively duplicates emitPseudoObjectRValue.
2926template <typename Impl, typename Result>
2927Result
2928ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visitPseudoObjectExpr(const PseudoObjectExpr *E) {
2929 SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData, 4> opaques;
2930
2931 // Find the result expression.
2932 const Expr *resultExpr = E->getResultExpr();
2933 assert(resultExpr);
2934 Result result;
2935
2936 for (PseudoObjectExpr::const_semantics_iterator
2937 i = E->semantics_begin(), e = E->semantics_end(); i != e; ++i) {
2938 const Expr *semantic = *i;
2939
2940 // If this semantic expression is an opaque value, bind it
2941 // to the result of its source expression.
2942 if (const OpaqueValueExpr *ov = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(semantic)) {
2943 typedef CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData OVMA;
2944 OVMA opaqueData;
2945
2946 // If this semantic is the result of the pseudo-object
2947 // expression, try to evaluate the source as +1.
2948 if (ov == resultExpr) {
2949 assert(!OVMA::shouldBindAsLValue(ov));
2950 result = asImpl().visit(ov->getSourceExpr());
2951 opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov,
2952 RValue::get(asImpl().getValueOfResult(result)));
2953
2954 // Otherwise, just bind it.
2955 } else {
2956 opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov, ov->getSourceExpr());
2957 }
2958 opaques.push_back(opaqueData);
2959
2960 // Otherwise, if the expression is the result, evaluate it
2961 // and remember the result.
2962 } else if (semantic == resultExpr) {
2963 result = asImpl().visit(semantic);
2964
2965 // Otherwise, evaluate the expression in an ignored context.
2966 } else {
2967 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(semantic);
2968 }
2969 }
2970
2971 // Unbind all the opaques now.
2972 for (unsigned i = 0, e = opaques.size(); i != e; ++i)
2973 opaques[i].unbind(CGF);
2974
2975 return result;
2976}
2977
2978template <typename Impl, typename Result>
2979Result ARCExprEmitter<Impl, Result>::visitBlockExpr(const BlockExpr *e) {
2980 // The default implementation just forwards the expression to visitExpr.
2981 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
2982}
2983
2984template <typename Impl, typename Result>
2985Result ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visitCastExpr(const CastExpr *e) {
2986 switch (e->getCastKind()) {
2987
2988 // No-op casts don't change the type, so we just ignore them.
2989 case CK_NoOp:
2990 return asImpl().visit(e->getSubExpr());
2991
2992 // These casts can change the type.
2993 case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
2994 case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
2995 case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
2996 case CK_BitCast: {
2997 llvm::Type *resultType = CGF.ConvertType(e->getType());
2998 assert(e->getSubExpr()->getType()->hasPointerRepresentation());
2999 Result result = asImpl().visit(e->getSubExpr());
3000 return asImpl().emitBitCast(result, resultType);
3001 }
3002
3003 // Handle some casts specially.
3004 case CK_LValueToRValue:
3005 return asImpl().visitLValueToRValue(e->getSubExpr());
3006 case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
3007 return asImpl().visitConsumeObject(e->getSubExpr());
3008 case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
3009 return asImpl().visitExtendBlockObject(e->getSubExpr());
3010 case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
3011 return asImpl().visitReclaimReturnedObject(e->getSubExpr());
3012
3013 // Otherwise, use the default logic.
3014 default:
3015 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
3016 }
3017}
3018
3019template <typename Impl, typename Result>
3020Result
3021ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *e) {
3022 switch (e->getOpcode()) {
3023 case BO_Comma:
3024 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(e->getLHS());
3025 CGF.EnsureInsertPoint();
3026 return asImpl().visit(e->getRHS());
3027
3028 case BO_Assign:
3029 return asImpl().visitBinAssign(e);
3030
3031 default:
3032 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
3033 }
3034}
3035
3036template <typename Impl, typename Result>
3037Result ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visitBinAssign(const BinaryOperator *e) {
3038 switch (e->getLHS()->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
3039 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
3040 return asImpl().visitBinAssignUnsafeUnretained(e);
3041
3042 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
3043 return asImpl().visitBinAssignWeak(e);
3044
3045 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
3046 return asImpl().visitBinAssignAutoreleasing(e);
3047
3048 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
3049 return asImpl().visitBinAssignStrong(e);
3050
3051 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
3052 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
3053 }
3054 llvm_unreachable("bad ObjC ownership qualifier");
3055}

3057/// The default rule for __unsafe_unretained emits the RHS recursively,
3058/// stores into the unsafe variable, and propagates the result outward.
3059template <typename Impl, typename Result>
3060Result ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::
3061 visitBinAssignUnsafeUnretained(const BinaryOperator *e) {
3062 // Recursively emit the RHS.
3063 // For __block safety, do this before emitting the LHS.
3064 Result result = asImpl().visit(e->getRHS());
3065
3066 // Perform the store.
3067 LValue lvalue =
3068 CGF.EmitCheckedLValue(e->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
3069 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(asImpl().getValueOfResult(result)),
3070 lvalue);
3071
3072 return result;
3073}

3075template <typename Impl, typename Result>
3076Result
3077ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visitBinAssignAutoreleasing(const BinaryOperator *e) {
3078 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
3079}
3080
3081template <typename Impl, typename Result>
3082Result
3083ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visitBinAssignWeak(const BinaryOperator *e) {
3084 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
3085}
3086
3087template <typename Impl, typename Result>
3088Result
3089ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visitBinAssignStrong(const BinaryOperator *e) {
3090 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
3091}

3093/// The general expression-emission logic.
3094template <typename Impl, typename Result>
3095Result ARCExprEmitter<Impl,Result>::visit(const Expr *e) {
3096 // We should *never* see a nested full-expression here, because if
3097 // we fail to emit at +1, our caller must not retain after we close
3098 // out the full-expression. This isn't as important in the unsafe
3099 // emitter.
3100 assert(!isa<ExprWithCleanups>(e));
3101
3102 // Look through parens, __extension__, generic selection, etc.
3103 e = e->IgnoreParens();
3104
3105 // Handle certain kinds of casts.
3106 if (const CastExpr *ce = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(e)) {
3107 return asImpl().visitCastExpr(ce);
3108
3109 // Handle the comma operator.
3110 } else if (auto op = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(e)) {
3111 return asImpl().visitBinaryOperator(op);
3112
3113 // TODO: handle conditional operators here
3114
3115 // For calls and message sends, use the retained-call logic.
3116 // Delegate inits are a special case in that they're the only
3117 // returns-retained expression that *isn't* surrounded by
3118 // a consume.
3119 } else if (isa<CallExpr>(e) ||
3120 (isa<ObjCMessageExpr>(e) &&
3121 !cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(e)->isDelegateInitCall())) {
3122 return asImpl().visitCall(e);
3123
3124 // Look through pseudo-object expressions.
3125 } else if (const PseudoObjectExpr *pseudo = dyn_cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(e)) {
3126 return asImpl().visitPseudoObjectExpr(pseudo);
3127 } else if (auto *be = dyn_cast<BlockExpr>(e))
3128 return asImpl().visitBlockExpr(be);
3129
3130 return asImpl().visitExpr(e);
3131}

3135/// An emitter for +1 results.
3136struct ARCRetainExprEmitter :
3137 public ARCExprEmitter<ARCRetainExprEmitter, TryEmitResult> {
3138
3139 ARCRetainExprEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF) : ARCExprEmitter(CGF) {}
3140
3141 llvm::Value *getValueOfResult(TryEmitResult result) {
3142 return result.getPointer();
3143 }
3144
3145 TryEmitResult emitBitCast(TryEmitResult result, llvm::Type *resultType) {
3146 llvm::Value *value = result.getPointer();
3147 value = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(value, resultType);
3148 result.setPointer(value);
3149 return result;
3150 }
3151
3152 TryEmitResult visitLValueToRValue(const Expr *e) {
3153 return tryEmitARCRetainLoadOfScalar(CGF, e);
3154 }
3155
3156 /// For consumptions, just emit the subexpression and thus elide
3157 /// the retain/release pair.
3158 TryEmitResult visitConsumeObject(const Expr *e) {
3159 llvm::Value *result = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(e);
3160 return TryEmitResult(result, true);
3161 }
3162
3163 TryEmitResult visitBlockExpr(const BlockExpr *e) {
3164 TryEmitResult result = visitExpr(e);
3165 // Avoid the block-retain if this is a block literal that doesn't need to be
3166 // copied to the heap.
3167 if (e->getBlockDecl()->canAvoidCopyToHeap())
3168 result.setInt(true);
3169 return result;
3170 }
3171
3172 /// Block extends are net +0. Naively, we could just recurse on
3173 /// the subexpression, but actually we need to ensure that the
3174 /// value is copied as a block, so there's a little filter here.
3175 TryEmitResult visitExtendBlockObject(const Expr *e) {
3176 llvm::Value *result; // will be a +0 value
3177
3178 // If we can't safely assume the sub-expression will produce a
3179 // block-copied value, emit the sub-expression at +0.
3180 if (shouldEmitSeparateBlockRetain(e)) {
3181 result = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(e);
3182
3183 // Otherwise, try to emit the sub-expression at +1 recursively.
3184 } else {
3185 TryEmitResult subresult = asImpl().visit(e);
3186
3187 // If that produced a retained value, just use that.
3188 if (subresult.getInt()) {
3189 return subresult;
3190 }
3191
3192 // Otherwise it's +0.
3193 result = subresult.getPointer();
3194 }
3195
3196 // Retain the object as a block.
3197 result = CGF.EmitARCRetainBlock(result, /*mandatory*/ true);
3198 return TryEmitResult(result, true);
3199 }
3200
3201 /// For reclaims, emit the subexpression as a retained call and
3202 /// skip the consumption.
3203 TryEmitResult visitReclaimReturnedObject(const Expr *e) {
3204 llvm::Value *result = emitARCRetainCallResult(CGF, e);
3205 return TryEmitResult(result, true);
3206 }
3207
3208 /// When we have an undecorated call, retroactively do a claim.
3209 TryEmitResult visitCall(const Expr *e) {
3210 llvm::Value *result = emitARCRetainCallResult(CGF, e);
3211 return TryEmitResult(result, true);
3212 }
3213
3214 // TODO: maybe special-case visitBinAssignWeak?
3215
3216 TryEmitResult visitExpr(const Expr *e) {
3217 // We didn't find an obvious production, so emit what we've got and
3218 // tell the caller that we didn't manage to retain.
3219 llvm::Value *result = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(e);
3220 return TryEmitResult(result, false);
3221 }
3222};
3223}

3226tryEmitARCRetainScalarExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *e) {

3230static llvm::Value *emitARCRetainLoadOfScalar(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3231 LValue lvalue,
3232 QualType type) {
3233 TryEmitResult result = tryEmitARCRetainLoadOfScalar(CGF, lvalue, type);
3234 llvm::Value *value = result.getPointer();

3240/// EmitARCRetainScalarExpr - Semantically equivalent to
3241/// EmitARCRetainObject(e->getType(), EmitScalarExpr(e)), but making a
3242/// best-effort attempt to peephole expressions that naturally produce
3243/// retained objects.
3244llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARCRetainScalarExpr(const Expr *e) {
3245 // The retain needs to happen within the full-expression.
3246 if (const ExprWithCleanups *cleanups = dyn_cast<ExprWithCleanups>(e)) {
3247 enterFullExpression(cleanups);
3248 RunCleanupsScope scope(*this);
3249 return EmitARCRetainScalarExpr(cleanups->getSubExpr());
3250 }
3251
3252 TryEmitResult result = tryEmitARCRetainScalarExpr(*this, e);
3253 llvm::Value *value = result.getPointer();
3254 if (!result.getInt())
3255 value = EmitARCRetain(e->getType(), value);
3256 return value;
3257}

3259llvm::Value *
3260CodeGenFunction::EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseScalarExpr(const Expr *e) {
3261 // The retain needs to happen within the full-expression.
3262 if (const ExprWithCleanups *cleanups = dyn_cast<ExprWithCleanups>(e)) {
3263 enterFullExpression(cleanups);
3264 RunCleanupsScope scope(*this);
3265 return EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseScalarExpr(cleanups->getSubExpr());
3266 }
3267
3268 TryEmitResult result = tryEmitARCRetainScalarExpr(*this, e);
3269 llvm::Value *value = result.getPointer();
3270 if (result.getInt())
3271 value = EmitARCAutorelease(value);
3272 else
3273 value = EmitARCRetainAutorelease(e->getType(), value);
3274 return value;
3275}
3276
3277llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARCExtendBlockObject(const Expr *e) {
3278 llvm::Value *result;
3279 bool doRetain;
3280
3281 if (shouldEmitSeparateBlockRetain(e)) {
3282 result = EmitScalarExpr(e);
3283 doRetain = true;
3284 } else {
3285 TryEmitResult subresult = tryEmitARCRetainScalarExpr(*this, e);
3286 result = subresult.getPointer();
3287 doRetain = !subresult.getInt();
3288 }
3289
3290 if (doRetain)
3291 result = EmitARCRetainBlock(result, /*mandatory*/ true);
3292 return EmitObjCConsumeObject(e->getType(), result);
3293}
3294
3295llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCThrowOperand(const Expr *expr) {
3296 // In ARC, retain and autorelease the expression.
3297 if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) {
3298 // Do so before running any cleanups for the full-expression.
3299 // EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseScalarExpr does this for us.
3300 return EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseScalarExpr(expr);
3301 }
3302
3303 // Otherwise, use the normal scalar-expression emission. The
3304 // exception machinery doesn't do anything special with the
3305 // exception like retaining it, so there's no safety associated with
3306 // only running cleanups after the throw has started, and when it
3307 // matters it tends to be substantially inferior code.
3308 return EmitScalarExpr(expr);
3309}

3382std::pair<LValue,llvm::Value*>
3383CodeGenFunction::EmitARCStoreUnsafeUnretained(const BinaryOperator *e,
3384 bool ignored) {
3385 // Evaluate the RHS first. If we're ignoring the result, assume
3386 // that we can emit at an unsafe +0.
3387 llvm::Value *value;
3388 if (ignored) {
3389 value = EmitARCUnsafeUnretainedScalarExpr(e->getRHS());
3390 } else {
3391 value = EmitScalarExpr(e->getRHS());
3392 }
3393
3394 // Emit the LHS and perform the store.
3395 LValue lvalue = EmitLValue(e->getLHS());
3396 EmitStoreOfScalar(value, lvalue);
3397
3398 return std::pair<LValue,llvm::Value*>(std::move(lvalue), value);
3399}
3400
3401std::pair<LValue,llvm::Value*>
3402CodeGenFunction::EmitARCStoreStrong(const BinaryOperator *e,
3403 bool ignored) {
3404 // Evaluate the RHS first.
3405 TryEmitResult result = tryEmitARCRetainScalarExpr(*this, e->getRHS());
3406 llvm::Value *value = result.getPointer();
3407
3408 bool hasImmediateRetain = result.getInt();
3409
3410 // If we didn't emit a retained object, and the l-value is of block
3411 // type, then we need to emit the block-retain immediately in case
3412 // it invalidates the l-value.
3413 if (!hasImmediateRetain && e->getType()->isBlockPointerType()) {
3414 value = EmitARCRetainBlock(value, /*mandatory*/ false);
3415 hasImmediateRetain = true;
3416 }
3417
3418 LValue lvalue = EmitLValue(e->getLHS());
3419
3420 // If the RHS was emitted retained, expand this.
3421 if (hasImmediateRetain) {
3422 llvm::Value *oldValue = EmitLoadOfScalar(lvalue, SourceLocation());
3423 EmitStoreOfScalar(value, lvalue);
3424 EmitARCRelease(oldValue, lvalue.isARCPreciseLifetime());
3425 } else {
3426 value = EmitARCStoreStrong(lvalue, value, ignored);
3427 }
3428
3429 return std::pair<LValue,llvm::Value*>(lvalue, value);
3430}
3431
3432std::pair<LValue,llvm::Value*>
3433CodeGenFunction::EmitARCStoreAutoreleasing(const BinaryOperator *e) {
3434 llvm::Value *value = EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseScalarExpr(e->getRHS());
3435 LValue lvalue = EmitLValue(e->getLHS());
3436
3437 EmitStoreOfScalar(value, lvalue);
3438
3439 return std::pair<LValue,llvm::Value*>(lvalue, value);
3440}

3442void CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCAutoreleasePoolStmt(
3443 const ObjCAutoreleasePoolStmt &ARPS) {
3444 const Stmt *subStmt = ARPS.getSubStmt();
3445 const CompoundStmt &S = cast<CompoundStmt>(*subStmt);
3446
3447 CGDebugInfo *DI = getDebugInfo();
3448 if (DI)
3449 DI->EmitLexicalBlockStart(Builder, S.getLBracLoc());
3450
3451 // Keep track of the current cleanup stack depth.
3452 RunCleanupsScope Scope(*this);
3453 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.hasNativeARC()) {
3454 llvm::Value *token = EmitObjCAutoreleasePoolPush();
3455 EHStack.pushCleanup<CallObjCAutoreleasePoolObject>(NormalCleanup, token);
3456 } else {
3457 llvm::Value *token = EmitObjCMRRAutoreleasePoolPush();
3458 EHStack.pushCleanup<CallObjCMRRAutoreleasePoolObject>(NormalCleanup, token);
3459 }
3460
3461 for (const auto *I : S.body())
3462 EmitStmt(I);
3463
3464 if (DI)
3465 DI->EmitLexicalBlockEnd(Builder, S.getRBracLoc());
3466}

3483/// GenerateObjCAtomicSetterCopyHelperFunction - Given a c++ object type with
3484/// non-trivial copy assignment function, produce following helper function.
3485/// static void copyHelper(Ty *dest, const Ty *source) { *dest = *source; }
3486///
3487llvm::Constant *
3488CodeGenFunction::GenerateObjCAtomicSetterCopyHelperFunction(
3489 const ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PID) {
3490 if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ||
3491 !getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.hasAtomicCopyHelper())
3492 return nullptr;
3493 QualType Ty = PID->getPropertyIvarDecl()->getType();
3494 if (!Ty->isRecordType())
3495 return nullptr;
3496 const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PID->getPropertyDecl();
3497 if ((!(PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_atomic)))
3498 return nullptr;
3499 llvm::Constant *HelperFn = nullptr;
3500 if (hasTrivialSetExpr(PID))
3501 return nullptr;
3502 assert(PID->getSetterCXXAssignment() && "SetterCXXAssignment - null");
3503 if ((HelperFn = CGM.getAtomicSetterHelperFnMap(Ty)))
3504 return HelperFn;
3505
3506 ASTContext &C = getContext();
3507 IdentifierInfo *II
3508 = &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("__assign_helper_atomic_property_");
3509
3510 QualType ReturnTy = C.VoidTy;
3511 QualType DestTy = C.getPointerType(Ty);
3512 QualType SrcTy = Ty;
3513 SrcTy.addConst();
3514 SrcTy = C.getPointerType(SrcTy);
3515
3516 SmallVector<QualType, 2> ArgTys;
3517 ArgTys.push_back(DestTy);
3518 ArgTys.push_back(SrcTy);
3519 QualType FunctionTy = C.getFunctionType(ReturnTy, ArgTys, {});
3520
3521 FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
3522 C, C.getTranslationUnitDecl(), SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), II,
3523 FunctionTy, nullptr, SC_Static, false, false);
3524
3525 FunctionArgList args;
3526 ImplicitParamDecl DstDecl(C, FD, SourceLocation(), /*Id=*/nullptr, DestTy,
3527 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3528 args.push_back(&DstDecl);
3529 ImplicitParamDecl SrcDecl(C, FD, SourceLocation(), /*Id=*/nullptr, SrcTy,
3530 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3531 args.push_back(&SrcDecl);
3532
3533 const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
3534 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(ReturnTy, args);
3535
3536 llvm::FunctionType *LTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
3537
3538 llvm::Function *Fn =
3539 llvm::Function::Create(LTy, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3540 "__assign_helper_atomic_property_",
3541 &CGM.getModule());
3542
3543 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, FI);
3544
3545 StartFunction(FD, ReturnTy, Fn, FI, args);
3546
3547 DeclRefExpr DstExpr(getContext(), &DstDecl, false, DestTy, VK_RValue,
3548 SourceLocation());
3549 UnaryOperator DST(&DstExpr, UO_Deref, DestTy->getPointeeType(),
3550 VK_LValue, OK_Ordinary, SourceLocation(), false);
3551
3552 DeclRefExpr SrcExpr(getContext(), &SrcDecl, false, SrcTy, VK_RValue,
3553 SourceLocation());
3554 UnaryOperator SRC(&SrcExpr, UO_Deref, SrcTy->getPointeeType(),
3555 VK_LValue, OK_Ordinary, SourceLocation(), false);
3556
3557 Expr *Args[2] = { &DST, &SRC };
3558 CallExpr *CalleeExp = cast<CallExpr>(PID->getSetterCXXAssignment());
3559 CXXOperatorCallExpr *TheCall = CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(
3560 C, OO_Equal, CalleeExp->getCallee(), Args, DestTy->getPointeeType(),
3561 VK_LValue, SourceLocation(), FPOptions());
3562
3563 EmitStmt(TheCall);
3564
3565 FinishFunction();
3566 HelperFn = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Fn, VoidPtrTy);
3567 CGM.setAtomicSetterHelperFnMap(Ty, HelperFn);
3568 return HelperFn;

3604
3605 FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
3606 C, C.getTranslationUnitDecl(), SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), II,
3607 FunctionTy, nullptr, SC_Static, false, false);
3608
3609 FunctionArgList args;
3610 ImplicitParamDecl DstDecl(C, FD, SourceLocation(), /*Id=*/nullptr, DestTy,
3611 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3612 args.push_back(&DstDecl);
3613 ImplicitParamDecl SrcDecl(C, FD, SourceLocation(), /*Id=*/nullptr, SrcTy,
3614 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3615 args.push_back(&SrcDecl);
3616
3617 const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
3618 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(ReturnTy, args);
3619
3620 llvm::FunctionType *LTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
3621
3622 llvm::Function *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(
3623 LTy, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, "__copy_helper_atomic_property_",
3624 &CGM.getModule());
3625
3626 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, FI);
3627
3628 StartFunction(FD, ReturnTy, Fn, FI, args);
3629
3630 DeclRefExpr SrcExpr(getContext(), &SrcDecl, false, SrcTy, VK_RValue,
3631 SourceLocation());
3632
3633 UnaryOperator SRC(&SrcExpr, UO_Deref, SrcTy->getPointeeType(),
3634 VK_LValue, OK_Ordinary, SourceLocation(), false);
3635
3636 CXXConstructExpr *CXXConstExpr =
3637 cast<CXXConstructExpr>(PID->getGetterCXXConstructor());
3638
3639 SmallVector<Expr*, 4> ConstructorArgs;
3640 ConstructorArgs.push_back(&SRC);
3641 ConstructorArgs.append(std::next(CXXConstExpr->arg_begin()),
3642 CXXConstExpr->arg_end());
3643
3644 CXXConstructExpr *TheCXXConstructExpr =
3645 CXXConstructExpr::Create(C, Ty, SourceLocation(),
3646 CXXConstExpr->getConstructor(),
3647 CXXConstExpr->isElidable(),
3648 ConstructorArgs,
3649 CXXConstExpr->hadMultipleCandidates(),
3650 CXXConstExpr->isListInitialization(),
3651 CXXConstExpr->isStdInitListInitialization(),
3652 CXXConstExpr->requiresZeroInitialization(),
3653 CXXConstExpr->getConstructionKind(),
3654 SourceRange());
3655
3656 DeclRefExpr DstExpr(getContext(), &DstDecl, false, DestTy, VK_RValue,
3657 SourceLocation());
3658
3659 RValue DV = EmitAnyExpr(&DstExpr);
3660 CharUnits Alignment
3661 = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(TheCXXConstructExpr->getType());
3662 EmitAggExpr(TheCXXConstructExpr,
3663 AggValueSlot::forAddr(Address(DV.getScalarVal(), Alignment),
3664 Qualifiers(),
3665 AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
3666 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
3667 AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
3668 AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap));
3669
3670 FinishFunction();
3671 HelperFn = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Fn, VoidPtrTy);
3672 CGM.setAtomicGetterHelperFnMap(Ty, HelperFn);
3673 return HelperFn;
3674}
3675
3676llvm::Value *
3677CodeGenFunction::EmitBlockCopyAndAutorelease(llvm::Value *Block, QualType Ty) {
3678 // Get selectors for retain/autorelease.
3679 IdentifierInfo *CopyID = &getContext().Idents.get("copy");
3680 Selector CopySelector =
3681 getContext().Selectors.getNullarySelector(CopyID);
3682 IdentifierInfo *AutoreleaseID = &getContext().Idents.get("autorelease");
3683 Selector AutoreleaseSelector =
3684 getContext().Selectors.getNullarySelector(AutoreleaseID);
3685
3686 // Emit calls to retain/autorelease.
3687 CGObjCRuntime &Runtime = CGM.getObjCRuntime();
3688 llvm::Value *Val = Block;
3689 RValue Result;
3690 Result = Runtime.GenerateMessageSend(*this, ReturnValueSlot(),
3691 Ty, CopySelector,
3692 Val, CallArgList(), nullptr, nullptr);
3693 Val = Result.getScalarVal();
3694 Result = Runtime.GenerateMessageSend(*this, ReturnValueSlot(),
3695 Ty, AutoreleaseSelector,
3696 Val, CallArgList(), nullptr, nullptr);
3697 Val = Result.getScalarVal();
3698 return Val;
3699}

3701llvm::Value *
3702CodeGenFunction::EmitBuiltinAvailable(ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> Args) {
3703 assert(Args.size() == 3 && "Expected 3 argument here!");
3704
3705 if (!CGM.IsOSVersionAtLeastFn) {
3706 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
3707 llvm::FunctionType::get(Int32Ty, {Int32Ty, Int32Ty, Int32Ty}, false);
3708 CGM.IsOSVersionAtLeastFn =
3709 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__isOSVersionAtLeast");
3710 }
3711
3712 llvm::Value *CallRes =
3713 EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(CGM.IsOSVersionAtLeastFn, Args);
3714
3715 return Builder.CreateICmpNE(CallRes, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int32Ty));
3716}
3717
3718void CodeGenModule::emitAtAvailableLinkGuard() {
3719 if (!IsOSVersionAtLeastFn)
3720 return;
3721 // @available requires CoreFoundation only on Darwin.
3722 if (!Target.getTriple().isOSDarwin())
3723 return;
3724 // Add -framework CoreFoundation to the linker commands. We still want to
3725 // emit the core foundation reference down below because otherwise if
3726 // CoreFoundation is not used in the code, the linker won't link the
3727 // framework.
3728 auto &Context = getLLVMContext();
3729 llvm::Metadata *Args[2] = {llvm::MDString::get(Context, "-framework"),
3730 llvm::MDString::get(Context, "CoreFoundation")};
3731 LinkerOptionsMetadata.push_back(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Args));
3732 // Emit a reference to a symbol from CoreFoundation to ensure that
3733 // CoreFoundation is linked into the final binary.
3734 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
3735 llvm::FunctionType::get(Int32Ty, {VoidPtrTy}, false);
3736 llvm::FunctionCallee CFFunc =
3737 CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "CFBundleGetVersionNumber");
3738
3739 llvm::FunctionType *CheckFTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {}, false);
3740 llvm::FunctionCallee CFLinkCheckFuncRef = CreateRuntimeFunction(
3741 CheckFTy, "__clang_at_available_requires_core_foundation_framework",
3742 llvm::AttributeList(), /*IsLocal=*/true);
3743 llvm::Function *CFLinkCheckFunc =
3744 cast<llvm::Function>(CFLinkCheckFuncRef.getCallee()->stripPointerCasts());
3745 if (CFLinkCheckFunc->empty()) {
3746 CFLinkCheckFunc->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage);
3747 CFLinkCheckFunc->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
3748 CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
3749 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(CGF.createBasicBlock("", CFLinkCheckFunc));
3750 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(CFFunc,
3751 llvm::Constant::getNullValue(VoidPtrTy));
3752 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3753 addCompilerUsedGlobal(CFLinkCheckFunc);
3754 }
3755}
